Manage local configuration

This command provides low level access to your local configuration file.

Usage:
  radio config set KEY VALUE
  radio config get KEY
  radio config del KEY
  radio config show
  radio config edit
  radio config check
  radio config guide
  radio config --help

Commands:
  get
    Show the value of this config key

  set
    Set the value of this config key

  del
    Delete the value of this config key

  show
    Show the entire config file contents

  edit
    Open the config file for editing

  guide
    Show a list of supported config keys and their purpose

  check
    Verify and report problems with the config file

Options:
  -s --show
    Show the contents of the config file

  -e --edit
    Open the config file for editing

  -h --help
    Show this help

Parameters:
  KEY
    Config key

  VALUE
    Config value

Examples:
  radio config edit
  radio config set like_log ~/like.log
  radio config del session_key
  radio config get listen_key
